     ,"INC-SPECT":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":null
	,"x4freetext":["The beam of an intensity of approximately 3.12*10**10"
		,"particles per second. The helium provided a negative"
		,"4He ion beam, generated through a helium plasma"
		,"extracted from a duoplasmatron followed by charge"
		,"exchange in a Li-vapor cell. The FN tandem has an"
		,"energy spread estimated to be 5 keV so that the total"
		,"energy spread can be estimated at 7 keV in the"
		,"laboratory frame, giving 4.5 keV in the"
		,"center-of-mass frame."]
	}
      ]
     ,"DETECTOR":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"SI", "dict":"DETECTOR", "idict":22,"hlp":"Silicon detector"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" Four Si detectors at laboratory angles of 30,"
		,"60, 90, and 135 degrees relative to the incident beam"
		,"direction."]
	}
      ]
     ,"SAMPLE":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4code":{"Nucl":"3-LI-7","ENR":0.9999}
	,"x4freetext":[" A 5 microg/cm2 target composed of"
		,"LiF with 99.99% enrichment in 7Li. The LiF was"
		,"evaporated onto a 20 microg/cm2 Carbon backing, which"
		,"was positioned downstream to prevent the energy loss"
		,"and straggling from impacting the quality of the"
		,"excitation functions. The main contaminants present"
		,"in the target were H, 12C, 16O and 19F. This target"
		,"thickness was chosen to ensure beam energy loss below"
		,"10 keV, providing high resolution in the excitation"
		,"function and characterizing the narrow resonance with"
		,"an expected width of about 20 keV. The energy loss"
		,"calculated with LISE++ is 4 keV in the laboratory frame"
		," (3 keV in the center-of-mass frame). Considering that"
		,"the target was tilted at 45 degrees to the beam"
		,"direction, the energy loss was below 5 keV."]
	}
      ]
     ,"METHOD":[
	{"x4pointer":" "
	 ,"x4codes":[{"code":"TOF", "dict":"METHOD", "idict":21,"hlp":"Time-of-flight"}]
	,"x4freetext":[" 15.4 cm flight path. The experiment was"
		,"conducted in the reaction chamber located in the"
		,"vault upstream of TriSol. The 7Li target foils were"
		,"positioned at the center of the chamber. To"
		,"compensate for the thin target thickness, each"
		,"detector had a solid angle of 13 msr. The absolute"
		,"cross-section normalization was obtained by"
		,"comparison with previous data from Cusson and Bohlen."]
	}
      ]
